  "text": "Although clinical trial data are available for other AIs, such as letrozole and exemestane, these data address primarily advanced breast cancer, with no data in primary adjuvant therapy. Although recent data in late adjuvant use after earlier tamoxifen have been published, these apply to a different population of patients than those addressed by the ATAC trial [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This aside, oncologists have taken results from these late adjuvant trials as supportive evidence for AIs in the adjuvant setting. At present anastrozole is the only AI with efficacy and safety data in the primary adjuvant setting. Other than anastrozole, adjuvant use of other hormonal agents did not increase during the period under study.",
